        <h2>Exercise</h2>
        <p>Regular physical activity improves overall well-being. Aim for at least 30 minutes of moderate exercise, such as walking, cycling, or yoga, most days of the week. Strength training exercises can also enhance muscle and bone health.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Mental Well-being</h2>
        <p>Mental health is just as important as physical health. Practice mindfulness, meditate, or spend time in nature to reduce stress. Stay connected with loved ones and seek professional help if needed.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Hydration</h2>
        <p>Water is essential for the body to function properly. Aim to drink at least 8 glasses of water a day, and more if you're active or in a hot climate.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Sleep</h2>
        <p>Quality sleep helps the body recover and rejuvenate. Ensure you get 7-9 hours of sleep each night by maintaining a consistent sleep schedule and creating a relaxing bedtime routine.</p>
